The offsite consequence analysis for the Water Filtration Plant includes consideration of two release scenarios for chlorine:
1. A Worst-Case Release
2. An Alternative Scenario

The following key elements outline the accidental release prevention program for the Donna Water Filtration Plant:

$    High level of training of the operators;
$    Preventive maintenance program;
$    Use of state-of-the-art process and safety equipment;
$    Use of accurate and effective operating procedures, written with the participation   of the operators;
$    Performance of a Process Hazard Analysis of equipment and procedures;
$    Implementation of an audit and inspection program.

As part of its Prevention Program 3, the Donna Water Filtration Plant maintains an employee participation plan, Pre-startup Procedures, Hot Work Permit Procedures, Management of Change, and a procedure for contractors working at the facility, as well as an emergency plan and documents relating to operating procedures and employee training. 

Prevention steps include operator use of the available SCBA during connection/disconnection of the chemical supply, awareness of the hazardous and toxic properties of chlorine, and the presence of a chemical detector. Donna Water Treatment Plant management has an agreement with Chemical Response & Remediation Contractors, Inc. (CRRC) for assistance with emergency response.

No accidental releases of chlorine have occurred at the site in the past five years.

